article_title: Notable & Quotable: The Disgraceful Stevens Prosecution
article_text:
From the Georgetown Law Journal’s “Annual Review of Criminal Procedure” (2015); Alex Kozinski, a judge on the U.S. Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals, writes in the preface about the 2008 federal case against Republican Sen. Ted Stevens, who died in 2010:

Senator Stevens was charged with corruption for accepting the services of a building contractor and paying him far below market price—essentially a bribe. The government’s...
